{"id":4231,"date":"2024-12-16T16:37:18","date_gmt":"2024-12-16T16:37:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=4231"},"modified":"2024-12-16T16:37:18","modified_gmt":"2024-12-16T16:37:18","slug":"power-items-upgrader","status":"publish","type":"wiki","link":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/misc-info\/useful-npcs\/power-items-upgrader\/","title":{"rendered":"Power Items Upgrader (NPC)"},"content":{"rendered":"<table class=\"table grey left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th>Location<\/th>\n<td><strong>Thundercap Mountain (Exterior)<\/strong> &#8211; East of Antisis City but outside Thundercap Mountain<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Purpose<\/th>\n<td>Upgrades your Power Items in exchange for Star Pieces and Comet Shards<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Transaction Item<\/th>\n<td>Star Pieces\/Comet Shards<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Cost<\/th>\n<td>Depends on the level of the Power Items<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Location<\/h2>\n<p>Fly to the Antisis City Pokemon Center and follow the path west.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/01-pokemon-unbound-standing-outside-of-the-antisis-city-pokemon-center.jpg\" alt=\"Standing outside of the Antisis City Pokemon Center. \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Standing outside of the Antisis City Pokemon Center.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Exit the city and cross the wooden bridge to the Thundercap Mountain area.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/02-pokemon-unbound-crossing-the-wooden-bridge-to-thundercap-mountain.jpg\" alt=\"Crossing the wooden bridge to Thundercap Mountain. \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Crossing the wooden bridge to Thundercap Mountain.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>The Power Items Upgrade NPC is the Black Belt NPC walking around south of the mountain\u2019s entrance.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/03-pokemon-unbound-approaching-the-power-items-upgrade-npc.jpg\" alt=\"Approaching the Power Items Upgrade NPC. \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Approaching the Power Items Upgrade NPC.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h2>Purpose<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/04-pokemon-unbound-upgrading-the-players-power-items.jpg\" alt=\"Upgrading the player\u2019s Power Items. \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Upgrading the player\u2019s Power Items.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Speaking with the Power Items Upgrade NPC for the first time initiates a battle. After you defeat his team of a Timburr and Crabominable, this NPC offers to upgrade your Power Items. This would include all EV-related Power Items like the Power Anklet, Power Band, etc.<\/p>\n<p>The upgrades initially will cost you Star Pieces. However, the transaction item switches from Star Pieces to Comet Shards after you upgrade a Power Item to level 7. Upgraded Power Items help your Pokemon gain more Effort Values when they\u2019re holding the item in battle.<\/p>\n<p>The table below details all the Power Items upgrades, including their cost and increased Effort Values.<\/p>\n<table class=\"table grey center zebra even-2col\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Item Level<\/th>\n<th>Cost<\/th>\n<th>EV Increase<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>2<\/td>\n<td>2 Star Pieces<\/td>\n<td>16<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3<\/td>\n<td>3 Star Piece<\/td>\n<td>24<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4<\/td>\n<td>4 Star Pieces<\/td>\n<td>32<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5<\/td>\n<td>5 Star Pieces<\/td>\n<td>40<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6<\/td>\n<td>6 Star Pieces<\/td>\n<td>48<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7<\/td>\n<td>7 Star Pieces<\/td>\n<td>56<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8<\/td>\n<td>2 Comet Shards<\/td>\n<td>64<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9<\/td>\n<td>3 Comet Shards<\/td>\n<td>72<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10<\/td>\n<td>4 Comet Shards<\/td>\n<td>80<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n\n        <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/misc-info\/useful-npcs\/\" class=\"parent-page-card\">\n            <picture class=\"card-img\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"300\" height=\"299\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/11\/useful-npc-preview.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/11\/useful-npc-preview.jpg 300w, https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/11\/useful-npc-preview-200x200.jpg 200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/>\t\t\t\t            <\/picture>\n            <span class=\"card-info\">\n                <span class=\"card-info__caption\">Back to:<\/span>\n                <strong class=\"wiki-title\">Useful NPCs<\/strong>\n            <\/span>\n        <\/a>\n\n\t\t\n","protected":false},"featured_media":4232,"parent":2143,"menu_order":2,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false},"categories":[],"class_list":["post-4231","wiki","type-wiki","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/4231","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/wiki"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/2143"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/4232"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4231"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=4231"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}